Author: LAING & BLACKWELL
Vol / Page: 294
Edition:
Quote: <i>Metrosideros umbellata </i>(The Southern Rata). A shrub or tree, 40-60 ft. high. ... Both islands, Auckland Islands. [formerly <i>M. lucida] ... Metrosideros umbellata</i>, the rata of the South Island, is known as the ironwood in Otago. It grows in masses on the slopes of the Southern Alps, and in a good rata year, adds much to the beauty of the scenery.
